\u4f1a\u6d25\u82e5\u677e\u99c5\u30fb\u4e09\u6625\u99c5\u307b\u304b (Koriyama Station, Aizu-Wakamatsu Station, Miharu Station, etc)|series=\u9031\u520a JR\u5168\u99c5\u30fb\u5168\u8eca\u4e21\u57fa\u5730|volume=50|date=2013-08-04|publisher=Asahi Newspaper Publishing|language=Japanese|asin=B00DNBCZL0|page=27}}</ref>\n\n==Station layout==\nThe station has a single [[island platform]] connected to the station building by an underground passage. The station is unattended.<ref name=\"zeneki50\"/> \n\n===Platforms===\n{{ja-rail-line|pfn=1|first=2|name= Ban'etsu East Line |linecol=mediumvioletred |dir= for {{STN| Ononiimachi}}, {{STN|Miharu}} and {{STN|K\u014driyama|Fukushima}}<br/>for {{STN|Iwaki|Fukushima}} (starting trains)}} \n{{ja-rail-line|pfn=2|first=3|nidx= Ban'etsu East Line |linecol=mediumvioletred |dir= for {{STN|Iwaki|Fukushima}}}}\n\n==History==\nOgawag\u014d Station opened on July 10, 1915. The station was absorbed into the JR East network upon the [[privatization]] of the [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR) on April 1, 1987.<ref name=\"zeneki50\"/> \n\n==Surrounding area==\n*{{jct|country=JPN|Route|399}}\n*Ogawa Post office\n*former Ogawa Town Hall\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Railway Stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Ogawago Station}}\n* {{Official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=359}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Ban'etsu East Line}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ogawago Station}} \n[[Category:Stations of East Japan Railway Company]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukushima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Ban'etsu East Line]] \n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1915]]\n[[Category:1915 establishments in Japan]]\n[[Category:Iwaki, Fukushima]]\n\n{{Fukushima-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Railway station in Iwaki, Fukushima Prefecture, Japan}}\n{{Refimprove|date=April 2018}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name        = Ogawag\u014d Station\n| native_name = \u5c0f\u5ddd\u90f7\u99c