==\nOgawag\u014d Station has a single [[island platform]] connected to the station building by an underground passage. The station is unattended.<ref name=\"zeneki50\"/> \n\n===Platforms===\n{{ja-rail-line|pfn=1|first=2|name= Ban'etsu East Line |linecol=purple|dir= for {{STN| Ononiimachi}}, {{STN|Miharu}} and {{STN|K\u014driyama|Fukushima}}<br/>for {{STN|Iwaki|Fukushima}} (starting trains)}} \n{{ja-rail-line|pfn=2|first=3|nidx= Ban'etsu East Line |linecol=purple|dir= for {{STN|Iwaki|Fukushima}}}}\n\n==History==\nOgawag\u014d Station opened on July 10, 1915. The station was absorbed into the JR East network upon the [[privatization]] of the [[Japanese National Railways]] (JNR) on April 1, 1987.<ref name=\"zeneki50\"/> \n\n==Surrounding area==\n*{{jct|country=JPN|Route|399}}\n*Ogawa Post office\n*former Ogawa Town Hall\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Railway Stations in Japan]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Ogawago Station}}\n* {{Official|1=http://www.jreast.co.jp/estation/station/info.aspx?StationCd=359}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Ban'etsu East Line}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ogawago Station}} \n[[Category:Stations of East Japan Railway Company]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Fukushima Prefecture]]\n[[Category:Ban'etsu East Line]] \n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1915]]\n[[Category:1915 establishments in Japan]]\n[[Category:Iwaki, Fukushima]]\n\n{{Fukushima-railstation-stub}}\n", "name_user": "MChew", "label": "safe", "comment": "copyedit", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ogawag%C5%8D_Station"}
